I think I found the code that implements it now. It's [this block](http://lxr.free-electrons.com/source/scripts/kconfig/menu.c#L341) inside `menu_finalize`. The following code checks the dependency on the "preceding" symbol:

    if (expr_depends_symbol(dep, sym))
        goto next;

When reading that code, it helps to know that `struct menu` represents any kind of menu *entry*. Each symbol will get a separate `struct menu` instance for example. How the `struct menu`s are connected determines the menu structure as seen in menuconfig.

