OK, I see you have the spec set up.
If you have not retrieved the DVPortgroup you wish to reconfigure, then that would be the next step.
And if you have not retrieved the DVSwitch that holds the DVPortgroup, that might be needed as well.

You can either navigate the inventory:
```
def GetDVSwitch(si, name):
   for dc in si.content.rootFolder.childEntity:
      for network in dc.networkFolder.childEntity:
         # I'm assuming you don't have network folders, if you do https://github.com/vmware/pyvmomi-community-samples/tree/master/samples has a lot of samples for get_obj function to use CreateContainerView
         if network.name == name:
            return network
   raise Exception("DVSwitch %s not found" % name)

def GetDVPortgroup(dvs, name):
   for portgroup in dvs.portgroup:
      if portgroup.name == name:
         return portgroup
   raise Exception("Portgroup %s not found." % name)

from pyVim.task import WaitForTask
dvs = GetDVSwitch(si, 'dvswitch')
dvportgroup = GetDVPortgroup(dvs, 'dvportgroup')
WaitForTask(dvportgroup.Reconfigure(dv_pg_spec))
```

