I think this can actually be solved purely using reactive states / flags:

```python
@when("config.changed.packages")
@when("apt.sources.configured")
@when_not("config.changed.sources")
def  install_packages():
    # ...

@when("config.changed.sources")
def configure_sources():
    # ...
    remove_state("config.changed.sources")
    set_state("apt.sources.configured")
```

This makes sense to me, as it's essentially saying, "We can install packages as long as we don't have any unprocessed changes to the sources list."

