@pde: Not sure if I really like that solution but on the other hand I will trust your judgment in the end. However one of the good things of systemd for me was the removal of shell scripts in /etc. These could be changed by the administrator but then this was also a recipe for problems when it comes to upgrades. I don't want to go there again.

Also grepping output seems really just like a band-aid (how do you ensure that "deploy cert" in your log file is actually a recent event and not one which happened months ago?). Having a proper hook looks much nicer to me and it exposes fewer internal details (the shell script itself, logging path). Also running a script regularly is just unnecessary when letsencrypt knows exactly when the event happens. And last but not least there is is a much bigger delay with a separat script.

