The issue is fixed by either making `~Foo` public, or by removing [these four lines](https://github.com/pybind/pybind11/blob/master/include/pybind11/pybind11.h#L1279) in the definition of class_::init_holder():

```
    /// Initialize holder object, variant 1: object derives from enable_shared_from_this
    template <typename T>
    static void init_holder(detail::instance *inst, detail::value_and_holder &v_h,
            const holder_type * /* unused */, const std::enable_shared_from_this<T> * /* dummy */) {
        try {
            auto sh = std::dynamic_pointer_cast<typename holder_type::element_type>(
                    v_h.value_ptr<type>()->shared_from_this());
            if (sh) {
                new (std::addressof(v_h.holder<holder_type>())) holder_type(std::move(sh));
                v_h.set_holder_constructed();
            }
        } catch (const std::bad_weak_ptr &) {}

        // XXX:Boris Commented to fix compile errors
        // if (!v_h.holder_constructed() && inst->owned) {
        //    new (std::addressof(v_h.holder<holder_type>())) holder_type(v_h.value_ptr<type>());
        //    v_h.set_holder_constructed();
        //}
    }
```

Although I am highly unfamiliar with all the template magic of pybind11, my understanding is that it is safe to comment these lines in my case since `Foo::shared_from_this()` should never fail and `sh` should never be null. But obviously, it is not an acceptable "fix" for pybind11 in the general case since I suppose it would break other use cases relying on these lines of code.

Any thoughts? Better fix?

For the time being, I'm using the following instead of commenting the lines, so I can at least be aware of potential issues during development:
```
        if (!v_h.holder_constructed() && inst->owned) {
            assert(false && "Unexpected nullptr or std::bad_weak_ptr exception after calling shared_from_this()");
            //new (std::addressof(v_h.holder<holder_type>())) holder_type(v_h.value_ptr<type>());
            //v_h.set_holder_constructed();
        }
```

